        "lessons": [
          {
            "title": "Lesson #1",
            "id": 132483,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Let's connect what we've learned about databases and backends so far. Now, we'll start working with a SQLite database within Node.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #2",
            "id": 132484,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We use an NPM package called <code>better-sqlite3</code> to help us interact with our database.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #3 - Copy",
            "id": 132490,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>First, we need to import it into our application using the <code>require</code> function.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"7\" /><option startIndex=\"8\" endIndex=\"24\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>require</code>, followed by <code>\"better-sqlite3\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #3",
            "id": 132485,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Next, we'll store the imported module in a variable <code>Database</code>, allowing us to interact with the SQLite database throughout our application.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"14\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>Database</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy",
            "id": 132491,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The next step is to initiate the database by creating a new instance of a SQLite database.</p><p>We create a new instance with the keyword <code>new</code> followed by the name of our variable. We also specify the name of the database file.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"44\" endIndex=\"47\" /><option startIndex=\"48\" endIndex=\"56\" /><option startIndex=\"57\" endIndex=\"72\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>new</code>, followed by <code>Database</code>, and finally <code>\"./database.db\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4",
            "id": 132486,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We define the location of the database file when creating a new one. <code>./</code> refers to the current directory.</p><p>This code will either load an existing database from the specified location or create a new one if it doesn't already exist.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"58\" endIndex=\"60\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>./</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy",
            "id": 132512,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We also store the new instance of the SQLite database in a new variable for easy access later.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"44\" endIndex=\"49\" /><option startIndex=\"50\" endIndex=\"52\" /><option startIndex=\"53\" endIndex=\"54\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>const</code>, followed by <code>db</code>, and finally <code>=</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #5",
            "id": 132487,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Now it's time to put everything to work! With <code>db.exec</code> we can run SQL statements such as creating tables or inserting data.</p><p>It doesn't return anything, though. But we don't need that when we want to create a new table.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" CREATE TABLE pets (name TEXT, species TEXT)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"87\" endIndex=\"89\" /><option startIndex=\"89\" endIndex=\"94\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>db</code>, followed by <code>.exec</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6",
            "id": 132488,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Use the <code>exec</code> method again to recreate the database you see here.</p><database visible-if=\"always\" bootstrapScript=\"CREATE TABLE Pets (&#xA;    name TEXT,&#xA;    species TEXT&#xA;);&#xA;&#xA;INSERT INTO Pets (name, species)&#xA;VALUES ('Tom', 'Cat');&#xA;\"><tables><table name=\"Pets\"><row><header content=\"name\" /><header content=\"species\" /></row><row><data content=\"Tom\" /><data content=\"Cat\" /></row></table></tables></database><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" CREATE TABLE pets (name TEXT, species TEXT)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" INSERT INTO pets (name, species)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" VALUES (&quot;Tom&quot;, &quot;Cat&quot;)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"147\" endIndex=\"149\" /><option startIndex=\"149\" endIndex=\"154\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>db</code>, followed by <code>.exec</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6 - Copy",
            "id": 132493,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Using <code>db.exec</code>, you can also add multiple values.</p><database visible-if=\"always\" bootstrapScript=\"CREATE TABLE Pets (&#xA;    name TEXT,&#xA;    species TEXT&#xA;);&#xA;&#xA;INSERT INTO Pets (name, species)&#xA;VALUES &#xA;    ('Tom', 'Cat'),&#xA;    ('Jerry', 'Mouse'),&#xA;    ('Spike', 'Dog'),&#xA;    ('Tweety', 'Bird');\"><tables><table name=\"Pets\"><row><header content=\"name\" /><header content=\"species\" /></row><row><data content=\"Tom\" /><data content=\"Cat\" /></row><row><data content=\"Jerry\" /><data content=\"Mouse\" /></row><row><data content=\"Spike\" /><data content=\"Dog\" /></row><row><data content=\"Tweety\" /><data content=\"Bird\" /></row></table></tables></database><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" CREATE TABLE pets (name TEXT, species TEXT)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" INSERT INTO pets (name, species)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" VALUES\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  (&quot;Tom&quot;, &quot;Cat&quot;),\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  (&quot;Jerry&quot;, &quot;Mouse&quot;),\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  (&quot;Spike&quot;, &quot;Dog&quot;),\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  (&quot;Tweety&quot;, &quot;Bird&quot;)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"147\" endIndex=\"154\" /></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>db.exec</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy",
            "id": 132494,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Require <code>better-sqlite3</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"17\" endIndex=\"24\" /><option startIndex=\"24\" endIndex=\"25\" /><option startIndex=\"25\" endIndex=\"41\" /><option startIndex=\"41\" endIndex=\"42\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"use\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>require</code> followed by <code>(</code> and then <code>\"better-sqlite3\"</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #14",
            "id": 132498,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What is the purpose of <code>db.exec</code>?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"> It executes a SQL command, such as creating tables or inserting data, without returning any result</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">It retrieves data from the database and returns the result</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\"> It executes a SQL command, such as creating tables or inserting data, without returning any result.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy",
            "id": 132495,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Create a new database called database.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"68\" endIndex=\"83\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"&quot;database&quot;\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>\"./database.db\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #15",
            "id": 132499,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What does <code>require(\"better-sqlite3\")</code> do?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">It imports the <code>better-sqlite3</code> module for SQLite database operations</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">It opens an existing SQLite database file</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">It imports the <code>better-sqlite3</code> module for SQLite database operations.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6 - Copy",
            "id": 132496,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Complete the code so we create a new database and add a first value.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;./database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" CREATE TABLE pets (name TEXT, species TEXT)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"db.exec(\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" INSERT INTO pets (name, species)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" VALUES (&quot;Tom&quot;, &quot;Cat&quot;)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"`\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"87\" endIndex=\"89\" /><option startIndex=\"89\" endIndex=\"90\" /><option startIndex=\"90\" endIndex=\"94\" /><option startIndex=\"147\" endIndex=\"149\" /><option startIndex=\"149\" endIndex=\"150\" /><option startIndex=\"150\" endIndex=\"154\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>db</code> followed by <code>.</code> and then <code>exec</code>, <code>db</code>, <code>.</code>, <code>exec</code>.</p></body></html>"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 15024,
        "title": "Querying a database",
        "type": "practiceLevel1",
        "lessons": [
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy",
            "id": 132510,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We'll now look at queries that return data, such as selecting data from a table.</p><p>When querying a database, we use the <code>prepare</code> method. This sets up the SQL statement so it can be executed later.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"db\" class=\"selector-tag\" /><text value=\".prepare\" class=\"selector-class\" /><text value=\"();\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"2\" /><option startIndex=\"2\" endIndex=\"10\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>db</code>, followed by <code>.prepare</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy - Copy",
            "id": 132513,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We pass the SQL query as a string as an argument to the <code>prepare</code> method.</p><p>Create a <code>SELECT</code> query and provide it as the argument.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"12\" endIndex=\"18\" /><option startIndex=\"19\" endIndex=\"20\" /><option startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"25\" /><option startIndex=\"26\" endIndex=\"31\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>SELECT</code> followed by <code>*</code> and then <code>FROM</code>, <code>users</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4",
            "id": 132503,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can save the prepared query in a variable.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" getUsersQuery = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"5\" /><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"19\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>const</code>, followed by <code>getUsersQuery</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #5",
            "id": 132504,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To run the query, call the <code>all</code> method on the prepared statement.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" getUsersQuery = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" users = getUsersQuery.all();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(users);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"71\" endIndex=\"84\" /><option startIndex=\"84\" endIndex=\"90\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"[\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  { id: 1, name: &quot;John Smith&quot; },\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  { id: 2, name: &quot;Jane Smith&quot; },\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  ...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"]\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>getUsersQuery</code>, followed by <code>.all()</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6",
            "id": 132505,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The <code>get</code> method is used to retrieve a single row from the result set.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" getUserByIdQuery = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" user = getUserByIdQuery.get();\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(user);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"103\" endIndex=\"106\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"{ id: 1, name: &quot;John Smith&quot; }\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>get</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6 - Copy",
            "id": 132515,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can also prepare a <code>SELECT</code> statement with parameters using question marks <code>?</code>. For example, to select a user by their <code>id</code>.</p><p>If we pass a value when executing the query, it will replace the question mark, allowing us to filter the results dynamically.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" getUserByIdQuery = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" user = getUserByIdQuery.get(\" /><text value=\"50\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(user);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"107\" endIndex=\"109\" /><option startIndex=\"68\" endIndex=\"69\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"{ id: 50, name: &quot;Pope Benedict XVI&quot; }\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>?</code>, followed by <code>50</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6 - Copy - Copy",
            "id": 132519,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>If we try to get an entry that doesn't exist, we receive <code>undefined</code>.</p><p>Try to query a user with the id <code>500</code> that will not return a value.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" getUserByIdQuery = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" user = getUserByIdQuery.get(\" /><text value=\"500\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(user);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"68\" endIndex=\"69\" /><option startIndex=\"107\" endIndex=\"110\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"undefined\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>?</code>, followed by <code>500</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #11",
            "id": 132520,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What does the <code>get</code> method do?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"> It retrieves a single row from the result set</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">It retrieves all rows from the result set</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\"> It retrieves a single row from the result set.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #12",
            "id": 132521,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What is the purpose of the question mark <code>?</code> in a prepared SQL query?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"> It acts as a placeholder for values that are passed when the query is executed</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">It indicates that the query is optional</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\"> It acts as a placeholder for values that are passed when the query is executed.</p></body></html>"
          },
